{
  "text": "A key finding of this study is that there are few risk factors for non-compliance with post-TOP care. This is in contrast with the risk factors for the need of subsequent TOP. [CITATION_1] Thus, comprehensive provision of both MTOP and post-TOP contraception (including IUD provision) is likely to be beneficial.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "37907451"
